Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 5:09 PM ET
Banks

Company Overview of Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A. provides financing, capital market, and investment banking services worldwide. The company’s investment banking services comprise mergers and acquisitions advisory, equity capital markets, and strategic equity transactions; and structured finance services include financing for air transportation and rail, shipping, real estate and lodging, natural resources, infrastructure, power, and energy sectors, as well as acquisition finance and tax based leasing. It is also involved in the sale and trading of products in primary and secondary markets for corporates, financial institutions, and large issuers; and provision of Renminbi services, includi...
Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A. provides financing, capital market, and investment banking services worldwide. The company’s investment banking services comprise mergers and acquisitions advisory, equity capital markets, and strategic equity transactions; and structured finance services include financing for air transportation and rail, shipping, real estate and lodging, natural resources, infrastructure, power, and energy sectors, as well as acquisition finance and tax based leasing. It is also involved in the sale and trading of products in primary and secondary markets for corporates, financial institutions, and large issuers; and provision of Renminbi services, including current account and cross-border transfers, FX, investment products, interest rate hedging products, and debt capital markets. The company’s transaction banking services comprise liquidity and working capital management services; trade finance services, such as guarantees, documentary transactions, structured trade finance, non-recourse purchase of trade receivables, and payable discounting, as well as a suite of e.Trade; and export and commodity finance services. Its debt optimization and distribution services comprise origination, structuring, and arrangement of syndicated, and bilateral medium-term and long-term loans; and underwriting of primary and secondary distribution of syndicated loans to banks and non-bank institutional investors. The company’s Islamic banking services include strategic advice, risk management, and capital raising. In addition, it offers wealth management services to high-net-worth and ultra-high-net-worth clients. The company was formerly known as Calyon and changed its name to Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A. in February 2010. The company was incorporated in 1973 and is headquartered in Montrouge, France. Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A. is a subsidiary of Credit Agricole S.A.
Detailed Description


