Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A. Key Developments

Credit Agricole CIB Global Markets Division Appoints Sebastien Lafosse as Head of Retail and Private Banking Group for the Americas
Jul 12 17
Credit Agricole CIB Global Markets Division announced that it has appointed Sebastien Lafosse as head of Retail and Private Banking Group for the Americas. In his new role based in New York, Lafosse will report locally to Stanislas Varin, head of Cross Asset Structuring and Koceila Maames, head of Financial Institutions Sales Americas. He reports globally to Regis Benichou, global head of Retail and Private Banking Group. Lafosse, who has more than 10 years' experience in Retail Distribution, has most recently been at Natixis SA heading the Cross Asset Solutions Distribution.


Crédit Agricole CIB Global Markets Division Hires Sebastien Lafosse as Head of Retail and Private Banking Group for the Americas
Jul 12 17
Crédit Agricole CIB Global Markets Division hires Sebastien Lafosse as Head of Retail and Private Banking Group for the Americas. Sebastien brings more than 10 years experience in the Retail Distribution space, starting his career at Société Générale as part of the Latin American structured products distribution, then on the Retail Structured Product team at Morgan Stanley and most recently at Natixis heading the Cross Asset Solutions Distribution.


Crédit Agricole CIB Hires Two New Strategists in New York
Jun 27 17
Crédit Agricole CIB hires two senior strategists in New York. Alex Li is appointed Head of US Rates Strategy for the Global Markets Research division in New York. As Head of US Rates Strategy for the Global Markets Research division, Alex will develop interest rate research products in the US. Alex’s career in strategy spans more than two decades in the US, covering a broad range of fixed income products with a focus on interest rates. He reports globally to Mohit Kumar, Global Head of Rates Strategy and locally to Christine Cremel, Global Markets Regional COO for the Americas. Prior to joining Crédit Agricole CIB, Alex was Chief US Treasury and Inflation Strategist at Deutsche Bank Securities, responsible for the development of client-facing interest rate research products in Treasuries, inflation-linked and interest rate futures, including strategy publications and quantitative models. Alex received his BS from the University of Toronto and his MS from Stanford University. Italo Lombardi has joined Crédit Agricole CIB as the Latin America economist and strategist based in New York. Italo does economic and financial market analysis, including macroeconomics, politics, FX and interest rates for the main economies of Latin America. He was the Latin America economist and strategist for more than five years at Standard Chartered, and previously at BNP Paribas in New York. He also worked at Roubini Global Economics. Italo holds a BA in economics from Ibmec Business School in Sao Paulo, Brazil. He reports globally to Sebastien Barbé, Head of Emerging Markets Research & Strategy, and locally to Christine Cremel, Global Markets Regional COO for the Americas.


