Company Overview of Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore provides corporate and investment banking products and services in Asia and internationally. It also offers fixed income and structured finance solutions, including structured trade finance facilities to international commodity traders, producers, refiners, importers, corporates, and financial institutions in Singapore and other countries of South-East Asia. Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore was formerly known as Banque Indosuez and changed its name to Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore in 1996. The company was founded in 1875 and is based in Singapore with branch offices in Singapore; and Labu...
Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore provides corporate and investment banking products and services in Asia and internationally. It also offers fixed income and structured finance solutions, including structured trade finance facilities to international commodity traders, producers, refiners, importers, corporates, and financial institutions in Singapore and other countries of South-East Asia. Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore was formerly known as Banque Indosuez and changed its name to Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank - Singapore in 1996. The company was founded in 1875 and is based in Singapore with branch offices in Singapore; and Labuan, Malaysia. It also has representative offices in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia; and Jakarta, Indonesia. Crédit Agricole Corporate & Investment Bank – Singapore operates as a subsidiary of Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A.
Detailed Description


